(firstQuint)Serotonin, Impulsivity, and Cocaine Dependence Treatment.

 Cocaine dependence continues to be a significant public health problem, for which there is no FDA approved pharmacotherapy.

 This study is a 12-week, double blind, placebo controlled trial of citalopram for cocaine dependence.

 The primary outcome measure is benzoylecgonine positive urines.

 Secondary measures of side effects and craving are also examined.

